Honeywell Flour Mills Plc, said it has put together the Honeywell Cook-Off Competition in boosting the food industry. The company in a release to media said “This is the first cooking competition to be executed in the Nigerian flour milling industry and it is currently exciting online foodies in Nigeria and across the globe. “The cooking competition, which is hosted by Tobi Bakare, a renowned social media influencer and 2018 Big Brother Naija finalist, has gained prominence on social media and in the food industry in the country.” The company stated that “The contestants in the show are expected to prepare delicacies made from Honeywell products with an emphasis on creativity and taste. “The contestants were chosen via an online chef hunt contest where they shared their dishes on social media and were then invited to the Honeywell Kitchen for the final round of the competition which will be in 5 different phases.” Managing director of Honeywell Flour Mills, Mr. Lanre Jaiyeola, said “We have put together the Honeywell Cook-Off Competition to engage food lovers all over the world and introduce them to the delicious, creative and nutritious meals that can be made using Honeywell food products.” Speaking on the selection process, Jaiyeola said, “The competition provided opportunities to upcoming chefs to showcase their talent and introduce distinctive Nigerian and international dishes to a wider audience.” Contestants will be rewarded with cash prizes and other consolation prizes. Honeywell Flour Mills Plc is  involved in milling, production, marketing and sales of high quality flour and wheat-based ambient, stable and packaged food products in the fast moving consumer goods (FMCG) space.